        <head xml:id="pl-l4d2c2-Hd1e109">CAP. II</head>
        <head xml:id="pl-l4d2c2-Hd1e112" type="question-title">
          Concerning baptism. On the difference between the baptism of John and Christ
        </head>
        <p xml:id="pl-l4d2c2-d1e115">
          Now let us see about the sacrament of baptism 
          which is first among sacraments of the new grace.
        </p>
        <p xml:id="pl-l4d2c2-d1e118">
          John announced the baptism of Christ in advance of 
          his own baptism, 
          which is first read to have baptized, <!-- translation confusing --> 
          but in water, not in the Spiritu, 
          just as he says: 
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="pl-l4d2c2-Qd1e122" source="http://scta.info/resource/mt3_11">
              I baptize you in the water into penticnece.
            </quote>
            <bibl>Matthaeus 3:11</bibl>
          </cit>.
          For he was only washing the body, 
          but was not cleansing from sin.
        </p>
